---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/inner.css';
---

<BaseLayout locale="en" localizedPaths={{ pt: '/sobre', en: '/en/sobre', es: '/es/sobre' }}
  title="About · Catalise.me"
  description="We exist to make AI cooperate with your company. We are not an agency, not a consultancy, and we do not sell software. We implement and help drive your results."
  ogTitle="About · Catalise.me"
  ogDescription="Why we exist and how we build systems that truly work." ogUrl="https://catalise.me/en/sobre" canonical="https://catalise.me/en/sobre"
  pageType="inner"
>

    <!-- HERO -->
    <header class="page-hero" aria-labelledby="sobre-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="eyebrow hero-animate-1">About Catalise.me</p>
        <h1 id="sobre-heading" class="page-hero-title hero-animate-2">
          We exist to <em>make AI cooperate with your company</em>.
        </h1>
        <p class="page-hero-lede hero-animate-3">
          We are not an agency, not a consultancy, and we do not sell software. We are the company that installs the system, integrates it with what you already have, trains your team, and monitors progress. We implement and help drive your results.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>


    <!-- A ORIGEM -->
    <section id="origem" aria-labelledby="origem-heading">
      <div class="container container-sm">
        <div class="section-header reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">The Origin</p>
          <h2 id="origem-heading">Why <em>we exist</em>.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="prose reveal">
          <p>Every growing company experiences the same syndrome. Each department buys its own tools, creates its own processes, generates its own data. What was agility becomes fragmentation. What was culture becomes silo.</p>
          <p>We spent years watching good businesses stall because of this. Brilliant owners becoming hostages of their own operations. Competent teams redoing work already done in another department. <strong>Good decisions made and forgotten. Customers complaining about the same problem another customer complained about last year.</strong></p>
          <p>We believed this was inevitable. It was the "price of growth." In 2024, with the leap of agentic AI, it became clear it is not. There is another way. <em>Intelligent systems can operate the company. Humans can return to strategic thinking.</em></p>
          <p>Catalise.me exists to make this transition happen: with method, responsibility, and real delivery. This is not an empty manifesto. It is the work we do, client by client, week by week.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- MANIFESTO -->
    <section id="manifesto" aria-labelledby="manifesto-heading">
      <div class="container container-sm">
        <div class="section-header reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Manifesto</p>
          <h2 id="manifesto-heading">The <em>five principles</em> that guide everything we deliver.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="principles-list">
          <div class="principle-item reveal">
            <span class="principle-num">01</span>
            <div class="principle-content">
              <h3>System beats effort</h3>
              <p>Every growing company depends less on the owner's personal effort and more on its operational system. We work toward this healthy disengagement: not to create dependency.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="principle-item reveal reveal-delay-1">
            <span class="principle-num">02</span>
            <div class="principle-content">
              <h3>Specific beats generic</h3>
              <p>We don’t believe in a "platform for any company." We specialize. Each niche with specific methods, correct terminology, native integrations. <strong>Generic is a trap.</strong></p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="principle-item reveal reveal-delay-2">
            <span class="principle-num">03</span>
            <div class="principle-content">
              <h3>We implement, not recommend.</h3>
              <p>Consultancies that deliver reports transfer the client’s problem back to the client. We <em>do</em>. When we leave, it’s running. That’s the contract.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="principle-item reveal reveal-delay-3">
            <span class="principle-num">04</span>
            <div class="principle-content">
              <h3>AI is a means, not an end</h3>
              <p>We use agentic AI as infrastructure. We don’t sell "artificial intelligence" as a product. Clients buy a functioning operation; AI is how we deliver it.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="principle-item reveal reveal-delay-4">
            <span class="principle-num">05</span>
            <div class="principle-content">
              <h3>We stay after delivery.</h3>
              <p>Installed and abandoned systems degrade. That’s why the Evolution Retainer is part of our proposal, not optional. Keeping agents calibrated, adding workflows, evolving alongside the business.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- COMO TRABALHAMOS -->
    <section id="como-trabalhamos" aria-labelledby="como-heading">
      <div class="container container-sm">
        <div class="section-header reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">How We Work</p>
          <h2 id="como-heading">Five practices that say <em>more than any speech</em>.</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="how-list">
          <div class="how-item reveal">
            <div class="how-icon"><i data-lucide="search" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
            <div class="how-content">
              <h3>Diagnosis before proposal.</h3>
               <p>We don’t send a quote without understanding your operation. The initial session is free for qualified profiles.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="how-item reveal reveal-delay-1">
            <div class="how-icon"><i data-lucide="clipboard-list" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
            <div class="how-content">
              <h3>Fixed scope.</h3>
               <p>The price is set before starting and does not change without a real reason. No surprise addendums.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="how-item reveal reveal-delay-2">
            <div class="how-icon"><i data-lucide="flag" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
            <div class="how-content">
              <h3>Small, dedicated team.</h3>
               <p>Quality comes from depth, not volume. We don’t outsource delivery.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="how-item reveal reveal-delay-3">
            <div class="how-icon"><i data-lucide="lock" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
            <div class="how-content">
              <h3>The system is yours.</h3>
               <p>Runs on your infrastructure, with your credentials. You are not hostage to us.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="how-item reveal reveal-delay-4">
            <div class="how-icon"><i data-lucide="target" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
            <div class="how-content">
              <p>We don’t sell to just anyone. Companies still validating their model or wanting results in 2 weeks are directed to other solutions.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA FINAL -->
    <section class="cta-section" aria-labelledby="sobre-cta-heading">
      <div class="container" style="position: relative; z-index: 1;">
        <p class="eyebrow" style="justify-content: center;">Next step</p>
        <h2 id="sobre-cta-heading">If it makes sense, the next step is <em>to talk</em>.</h2>
        <p>The diagnosis is free and takes 45 minutes. You leave with a map of your bottlenecks and a plan to solve them. No obligation to proceed.</p>
        <div class="cta-buttons">
          <a href="/en/contato" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" id="sobre-cta-primary">
            Schedule free diagnosis <span class="btn-arrow">→</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/en/opera-os" class="btn btn-secondary btn-lg" id="sobre-cta-secondary">
            See Opera OS in detail
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

</BaseLayout>
